activity with HSP90 or HSP70 as substrates. By phosphorylating HSPs in the 
foldosome complex, MAPK1 may regulate the stability and activity of the 
foldosome which in turn plays a pivotal role in the parasitic life cycle of L. 
donovani. Our study therefore implicates LdMAPK1 in the post-translational 
modification and possibly the regulation of heat shock proteins. Conversely, 
HSP90 and HSP70 are identified as the first substrates of LdMAPK1.

