Covered biliary stents with proximal bare stent extension for the palliation of 
malignant biliary disease: can we reduce tumour overgrowth rate?

Krokidis M(1), Hatzidakis A(2).

Author information:
(1)Department of Radiology, Cambridge University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust, 
Cambridge, UK. mkrokidis@hotmail.com.
(2)Department of Medical Imaging and Interventional Radiology, University 
Hospital of Heraklion, Medical School of Crete, Heraklion, Greece.

BACKGROUND: Covered biliary stents have shown significant effectiveness in the 
palliative management of patients with malignant biliary disease due to 
prevention of tumour ingrowth. However, stent dysfunction may still occur due to 
growth of tumour at the borders of the covered stent (tumour overgrowth). The 
aim of this study is to assess the effectiveness of a bare extension in the 
prevention of tumour overgrowth when covered stents are used in the palliative 
treatment of malignant biliary strictures.
